text: ANFA may refer to: In football: *All Nepal Football Association, the governing body of football in Nepal *Asociación Nacional de Fútbol Amateur, the governing body of Chilean football In finance: *Agreement on Net Financial Assets, an agreement between the European Central Bank and central banks in the Eurozone In architecture: *Academy of Neuroscience for Architecture == See also == * Anfa, an ancient toponym for Casablanca
title: ANFA
